{"word":"δυσμενής","slug":"δυσμενής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>δυσμενής</b></el> <el>(δυς-μενής, ές) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:μένος'><el>μένος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>full of ill-will, hostile</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>; rarely <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>ἄνδρα δ. χθονός</el> <i>an enemy of</i> the land, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>rarely of things, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}